hopobject.body: When do you want me to start? buy designer drugs online uk A strong first-half was driven by contracts with the Government’s “welfare to work” scheme aimed at helping the unemployed into employment. These contracts are guaranteed for five years from June 2011 and are based on a payment by results. Staffline’s subsidiary Eos got the top rating and its operating profits in the first half were £734,000, from a loss last time round. Staffline chief executive Andy Hogarth expects Eos to generate £2m for the full-year.
